The paper deals with lower bounds for data-dependent Locality-Sensitive Hashing schemes, which are primarily used in data structures and algorithms for efficient nearest neighbor search. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). The paper also involves information theory (cs.IT) and computational geometry (cs.CG) in the analysis of the hash functions. Additionally, the paper deals with lower bounds for hashing, which is a topic in discrete mathematics (cs.DM). Finally, the paper involves machine learning techniques, which are often studied in the category of machine learning (cs.LG).
